messages.message:
Hey, connected with @Subash
The actual error was incorrect version of `protobuf`, that lead to the compilation error for the `ibdoc_to_json` package
So, we unlinked the `protbuf` , and when reinstalling we faced issues related to brew
There was a update related to `xcode` pending, which subash is installing, we will test again after that's done + system restart
interesting, i think jessica also ran into issues last week because of an incorrect version of `protobuf`  https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/60358#discussion_r1690345646
@Abhishek updating `xcode`  and `protobuf` dint work. Still facing the same issue
I think I have fixed it. Deleting the build folder of `ibdoc_to_json`   module,  triggered a rebuilt which fixed the issue
